## 📊 Baseline SCADA vs. Sentinel AI Engine Benchmark

| Evaluation Metric | Traditional SCADA (Baseline) | Sentinel AI Engine |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Gas Telemetry (Sensor S102)** | `91 ppm` — **SAFE** (Below 100 ppm trip limit) | `91 ppm` — **ELEVATED** (Weighted compound score) |
| **Permit State (Permit P101)** | `APPROVED` — Hot Work active | `HIGH HAZARD OVERLAP` — Ignition source active |
| **Overall Assessment** | 🟢 **NORMAL OPERATIONAL STATE** | 🔴 **CRITICAL RISK (90%)** |
| **System Action** | No action. System waits for explosion or 100+ ppm spike. | **Automated Permit Revocation & Zone Evacuation Initiated.** |
| **Core Value** | *Silo Blindspot:* Ignores spark source in gas zone. | *Cross-Domain Intelligence:* Preemptively prevents ignition. |

